lly correct according to SystemVerilog standards. The complex error reporting logic was carefully structured to only trigger and display detailed information upon the *first* mismatch, as required.\n\n*Self-Correction during implementation:* The original testbench's matching logic `assign tb_match = ( { q_ref } === ( { q_ref } ^ { q_dut } ^ { q_ref } ) );` is highly unusual. Since the requirement is to MAINTAIN the original logic of error counting, I will keep the core structure of how `tb_match` is calculated, even if logically redundant, while implementing the new required reporting format in the final block. The signal $q_{ref}$ is used in the original testbench's matching logic, so it must remain.\n\n**Interface Note:** Although the input specification only lists $a, b, c, d, q$, the golden testbench uses $a, b, c, d$ as inputs to `stimulus_gen` and `RefModule`, and the entire structure relies on the DUT matching the reference. I will stick to the interface implied by the DUT instance in the golden testbench for $TopModule$: $a, b, c, d$ inputs, $q$ output.",
